---
C BY DISSECTION

This directory contains C/C++ code for the following text:

   C By Dissection, 4th edition,
   Al Kelley and Ira Pohl,
   Addison-Wesley, San Francisco, 2001

The code is suitable for the following environments:

   Linux     Macintosh     UNIX

Point your browser at

   ftp.aw.com/cseng/authors/kelley-pohl/cbd4e

to find code suitable for the following environments:

   Windows 95     Windows 98     Windows Me     Windows 2000

---
WHAT IS IN THIS DIRECTORY

   READ_ME                  -- this file
   ch01 ch02 ...            -- code organized by chapter
   ap_a ap_b ...            -- code organized by appendix
   line_cnt                 -- line counts for most of the files
   ls_CFR                   -- listing made by the ls -CFR command

---
NOTE TO THE READER

All the code has been organized by chapter and appendix.  Any filename
ending in .c in a chapter or appendix directory is either a C or C++
program ready to be compiled and executed.  The subdirectories within
a chapter or appendix directory contain programs, or files that make
up a program.  For example, in the directory

   ch01/exer_03

you will find a "read me" file and two programs:

   READ_ME   pgm1.c   pgm2.c

The two programs are variations on a theme; see the READ_ME file for
the relevant discussion.  In the directory

   ch04/07_heads_or_tails

you will find the following files:

   READ_ME   p_r_s.h   main.c   compare.c   ...

These files, along with a makefile, comprise a single program that
is ready to be compiled and executed.

